Atul Gawande is a surgeon, writer, and public health researcher and author of <em>Better</em>. He practices general and endocrine surgery at Brigham and Womens Hospital in Boston. He is <span id="1892dc90-6a8b-4f2a-a276-358e999fc88a" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="29cfc6f5-0fa3-42a0-a6a8-1496e4465af5" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="ae4cc94d-ccff-48a1-8298-12ca22c15aa2" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="a0a3031e-4675-44d5-9946-d777c2e9e750" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="82bdb9be-c814-483f-8346-6ecb546939f8" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="f88e8779-6bd1-412d-ae2a-244888ead9ae" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="bf61c4f1-9c9f-4a22-9e72-66b46807d056" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark">Professor</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> in the Department of Health Policy and Management at the Harvard School of Public Health and Professor of Surgery at Harvard Medical School. He is Executive Director of Ariadne Labs, a joint center for health systems innovation at Brigham and Womans Hospital and Harvard School of Public Health. And he is also co-founder and chairman of Lifebox, an international not-for-profit implementing systems and technologies to reduce surgical deaths <span id="dbfd9120-4084-44bc-9347-2edde7df4db5" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="f94e4ca1-711f-4b2c-9cb5-58f5c3bc2c54" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="52b18d91-252d-4b1a-adff-00d004d8c9d7" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="bdd2e86d-59d3-4bac-80c6-cf0c53e3cd9a" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="0cbb5d6e-f876-4e9e-abdb-802cab48c43e" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="961842cb-0706-480e-a8c6-d8c51b8aee87" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span id="d437f83b-928a-4029-af6c-c9ce4fca8629" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark">globally</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>. You can learn more about his background on <a title="Atul Gawande's Wikipedia page" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atul_Gawande" target="_blank">his Wikipedia page</a>.

